Statistics-Sequences version 0.042
=================================

Tests of sequential structure in the form of runs, joins, bunches, etc.
Includes the Wald-Walfowitz Runs test, Helmut Schmidt's test of the "potential energy", or pot, of runs, and I. J. Good's version of the Serial Test for "v-nomes".
Test of significance are typically limited to approximations from the normal distribution, or as chi-square.
Provides methods for dichotomising data where relevant for testing runs and joins.

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

   perl Makefile.PL
   make
   make test
   make install

DEPENDENCIES

This module requires these other modules and libraries:

  Statistics::Zed
  Statistics::Distributions
  Statistics::Lite
  Math::Cephes
  Algorithm::Combinatorics
  Scalar::Util

